description: Latin incidere; prefix in- (“in”) + caedere (“to cut”). See concise, and compare incise.

verbs.description: incide (third-person singular simple present incides, present participle inciding, simple past and past participle incided)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To cut; to separate and remove.
(obsolete) To resolve or break up, as by medicines.
examples: all Saponaceous Substances , which incide the Mucus in the first Passages
